div#billing-mapping-step
  .header-container-mapping
    h4.import-modal-header Map Spreadsheet Columns – Billing
    p.import-modal-subtext.text-muted
      | This billing mode only needs two columns. The anchor field depends on your
      | selected <em>Billing Type</em> (Household or Account).

  // Render only two fields: dynamic anchor + Amount.
  div#billing-mapping-fields-container
    .d-flex.mb-4.required-container-cards
      .required-field-card.border.p-3.me-3
        .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
          i.fas.fa-id-card.fa-lg.me-2.text-primary
          h6.m-0
            | <span id='billing-anchor-label'>Anchor ID</span>
        small.text-muted.databox-sub.map-sub
          | Required. If Household → Household ID. If Account → Account Number.
        select#billing-anchor-select.form-select(name='billingAnchor', data-required='true')
          option(value='') -- Select Column --

      .required-field-card.border.p-3
        .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
          i.fas.fa-dollar-sign.fa-lg.me-2.text-success
          h6.m-0 Amount
        small.text-muted.databox-sub.map-sub Numeric billed amount
        select#billing-amount-select.form-select(name='amount', data-required='true')
          option(value='') -- Select Column --

  small.text-muted.d-block.mt-2
    | Only the above two columns are needed for billing imports.
